# PHASE 8: Execution Instructions

## Task 8.1: Orchestrator Execution Protocol

    DECLARE execution_protocol: object

    SET execution_protocol.step_1 = {
        "action": "Create artifact directory",
        "command": "mkdir -p .claude/workspace/refactor-validation"
    }

    SET execution_protocol.step_2 = {
        "action": "Create core documents",
        "documents": core_documents
    }

    SET execution_protocol.step_3 = {
        "action": "Execute Phase 1 agent",
        "tool": "Task",
        "params": {
            "subagent_type": "code-tracer-agent",
            "prompt": "Analyze codebase-validation architecture. Read ARCHITECTURAL-ASSESSMENT.md purpose. Map current BaseScanner, BaseValidator, BaseAutoFixer flows to required algorithms from _DEV-RULES-ALGORITHMS.md. Document gaps in ARCHITECTURAL-ASSESSMENT.md. Map current settings.json usage in SETTINGS-INTEGRATION.md."
        }
    }

    SET execution_protocol.step_4_5 = {
        "action": "Continue with remaining agents",
        "pattern": "Read handoff context, execute phase, signal completion"
    }

    SET execution_protocol.final = {
        "action": "Verify completion",
        "command": "npm run verify-codebase",
        "expected": "All checks pass with algorithm-compliant architecture"
    }

## Task 8.2: First Time Initiation

    IF first_time:
        REPORT workflow_summary WITH:
            - 5 agents in sequence
            - Critical: BaseAutoFixer State-Snapshot-Recovery
            - High: BaseScanner Perceptual-Loop
            - High: BaseValidator Verification-Gate-Protocol
            - Medium: Migrate all implementations
            - Final: Compliance verification

        READ user_choice FROM user_prompt "Review complete. Next action: [Execute Workflow] [Edit Template] [Cancel]?"

        IF user_approves:
            EXECUTE workflow FROM step_1

    VALIDATION GATE:
        ✅ execution_protocol complete
        ✅ first_time_initiation defined
        ✅ user_approval_required

# ALWAYS RULES

ALWAYS read algorithm specifications BEFORE implementation
ALWAYS verify settings backward compatibility
ALWAYS include semantic guarantees in JSDoc
ALWAYS run npm run verify-codebase AFTER changes
ALWAYS use Task tool FOR agent execution
ALWAYS maintain single source of truth IN documents
NEVER modify existing API signatures WITHOUT deprecation
NEVER skip safety validation IN auto-fixers
NEVER hardcode values that should be configurable
NEVER remove existing settings keys
ALWAYS create backup BEFORE destructive operations
ALWAYS document new settings IN schema
